Anysphere Raises $60M For AI-Powered Coding Tool, Cursor
  URL: https://www.maginative.com/article/anysphere-raises-60m-for-ai-powered-coding-tool-cursor/
  This latest funding brings Anysphere's total raise to over $71 million, following an $8 million seed round last September led by OpenAI.

  --- Content ---
  Anysphere, a rising star in the AI coding assistant space, and the startup behind [Cursor](https://www.cursor.com/?ref=maginative.com), has announced a significant milestone—raising $60 million in a Series A funding round. The funding, led by Andreessen Horowitz, includes notable contributions from Google’s Jeff Dean, OpenAI’s John Schulman and Noam Brown, and the founders of Stripe and GitHub, among others.
  
